I will set up a sub class of the Command.cmd module called "Command"
this will handle the inputs and pass info to the controller.
I will take all the methods out of the controller class related to Command.Cmd module and make them available to the Command class

This change will see the following methods moved to a class called Command.

do_view_records(self, arg)
do_view_options(self, arg)
do_graphic_gender_pie_chart(self, arg)
do_graphic_age_bar_chart(self, arg)
do_select_rec(self, arg)
do_select_option(self, arg)
do_text_load(self, arg)
do_text_save(self, arg)
do_serial_load(self, arg)
do_serial_save(self, arg)
do_add_rec(self, arg)
do_edit_age(self, arg)
do_edit_sales(self, arg)
do_edit_bmi(self, arg)
do_edit_income(self, arg)
do_on(self, arg)
do_off(self, arg)
do_neutral(self, arg)
do_exit(self, arg)
do_help(self, arg)

This is because do_ commands are part of the Command.Cmd module

i will also make a method in the Command class called "Show", since Command.Cmd provides methods for input.


